## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa7e7-113">次の例では<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> 、要素を使用し<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>て、国/地域名を含む要素のリストを作成します。これらのうちいずれかを使用して、含まれている語句を認識します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa7e7-113">The following example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> element to build lists of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> elements containing country/region names, any one of which may be used to recognize the containing phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa7e7-114">次に、結果として得<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>られるオブジェクトの1つを、欧州および南アメリカの国/地域に対応するルールに追加します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa7e7-114">The example then adds one of the resulting <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects to their respective rules for European and South American countries/regions.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa7e7-115">さらに、この例では<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> 、オブジェクトを使用して`ruleEurope`ルール`ruleSAmerica`参照を2つの代替候補の一覧にグループ化しています。どちらか一方を使用して、音声入力を認識できます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa7e7-115">Further on, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to group rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` into a list of two alternatives, either one of which may be used to recognize spoken input.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa7e7-119">次の例では、"ワールドカップを獲得した国" という語句を認識する文法を作成し、その後にワールドカップを獲得した国/地域の名前を指定します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa7e7-119">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country/region that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa7e7-120">これにより、という`WorldCupWinner`名前のパブリックルールが作成されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa7e7-120">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa7e7-121">次に、新しい<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>オブジェクトの<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>配列を含むオブジェクトを使用して、2つのオブジェクトを作成します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa7e7-121">It then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects that contain arrays of new <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa7e7-122">この例で生成される文法を確認する<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>には、「」を参照してください。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa7e7-122">To see the grammar that this example generates, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
 public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
